  "bio_raw": "Ms. Sameera Zaman is a Lecturer-cum-Research Associate at the Center for Sustainable Development. She is an experienced environmental and social researcher, with a Bachelor’s degree in Environmental Management from Independent University, Bangladesh, and a Master’s in Environmental Sciences from the University of Freiburg, Germany. By employing different research tools and designs, she manages to pursue her passion in finding sustainable solutions to new-age problems and understanding the complex nature of the environment and its interactions.\nHer previous work experience in Research includes working as a Graduate Research Assistant for a few years at the Institute of Hydrology, Chair of Landscape Ecology and Nature Conservation as well as the Chair of Remote Sensing and Landscape Information Systems. In Bangladesh, Ms. Zaman has conducted research on diverse thematic areas including sustainable fashion, implementation of the circular design, and socio-economic impacts of climate change. Apart from research, her previous professional experience includes working with gender equality and disaster management in the development sector, in addition to working with Environmental Management Systems in different industries.",
